      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A powerful, multi-antenna router certainly has the capability to broadcast a very strong signal, which can make signal strength variations more pronounced when moving between rooms. Signal triangulation requires *multiple* known access points to pinpoint a location, so one powerful router alone doesn't equate to constant personal surveillance. It is more probable that you are experiencing standard radio wave propagation patterns influenced by the room layout.",
      "source": "target",
